      • createPrototype

        public <BEAN extends Bean> BEAN createPrototype(Class<BEAN> type)
        Description copied from interface: BeanFactory
        Creates a prototype of the given Bean. A prototype is used as template to create regular Beans. Such beans will inherit the defaults from the prototype what are the available properties as well as their default value.
        While in regular Java there is a separation between a Class for reflection and its Object instance, this approach makes it a lot easier. The prototype is like the Class where Bean-instances can be created of that are of the same type.
        Specified by:
        createPrototype in interface BeanFactory
        Type Parameters:
        BEAN - the generic type of the Bean.
        Parameters:
        type - the Class reflecting the Bean.
        Returns:
        the prototype instance of the specified Bean.
        See Also:
        BeanPrototypeBuilder.createPrototype(Class, String, Bean...)

      • getPrototypeInternal

        protected <BEAN extends Bean> BeanAccessPrototypeInternal<BEAN> getPrototypeInternal(Class<BEAN> type)
        Gets the initial internal and not-dynamic BeanAccessPrototype. Using a WeakHashMap as cache to avoid memory leaking and a ReentrantLock to be thread-safe.
